{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# scipy.integrate.odeint example\n",
    "\n",
    "To make the animation, do:\n",
    "\n",
    "`conda install -c conda-forge ffmpeg`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy import integrate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "from matplotlib import animation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N_trajectories = 20"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def lorentz_deriv(coords, t0, sigma=10., beta=8./3, rho=28.0):\n",
    "    x,y,z = coords\n",
    "    out = [sigma * (y - x), x * (rho - z) - y, x * y - beta * z]\n",
    "    return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Choose random starting points, uniformly distributed from -15 to 15\n",
    "np.random.seed(1)\n",
    "x0 = -15 + 30 * np.random.random((N_trajectories, 3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Solve for the trajectories\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, 4, 1000)\n",
    "x_t = np.asarray([integrate.odeint(lorentz_deriv, x0i, t)\n",
    "                  for x0i in x0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Set up figure & 3D axis for animation\n",
    "fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "ax = fig.add_axes([0, 0, 1, 1], projection='3d')\n",
    "ax.axis('off');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# choose a different color for each trajectory\n",
    "colors = plt.cm.jet(np.linspace(0, 1, N_trajectories))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# set up lines and points\n",
    "lines = sum([ax.plot([], [], [], '-', c=c)\n",
    "             for c in colors], [])\n",
    "pts = sum([ax.plot([], [], [], 'o', c=c)\n",
    "           for c in colors], [])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(5, 55)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# prepare the axes limits\n",
    "ax.set_xlim((-25, 25))\n",
    "ax.set_ylim((-35, 35))\n",
    "ax.set_zlim((5, 55))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# set point-of-view: specified by (altitude degrees, azimuth degrees)\n",
    "ax.view_init(30, 0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# initialization function: plot the background of each frame\n",
    "def init():\n",
    "    for line, pt in zip(lines, pts):\n",
    "        line.set_data([], [])\n",
    "        line.set_3d_properties([])\n",
    "\n",
    "        pt.set_data([], [])\n",
    "        pt.set_3d_properties([])\n",
    "    return lines + pts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# animation function.  This will be called sequentially with the frame number\n",
    "def animate(i):\n",
    "    # we'll step two time-steps per frame.  This leads to nice results.\n",
    "    i = (2 * i) % x_t.shape[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for line, pt, xi in zip(lines, pts, x_t):\n",
    "        x, y, z = xi[:i].T\n",
    "        line.set_data(x, y)\n",
    "        line.set_3d_properties(z)\n",
    "\n",
    "        pt.set_data(x[-1:], y[-1:])\n",
    "        pt.set_3d_properties(z[-1:])\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.view_init(30, 0.3 * i)\n",
    "    fig.canvas.draw()\n",
    "    return lines + pts"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# instantiate the animator.\n",
    "anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init,\n",
    "                               frames=500, interval=30, blit=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Save as mp4. This requires mplayer or ffmpeg to be installed\n",
    "filename = 'lorentz_attractor.mp4'\n",
    "anim.save(filename, fps=15, extra_args=['-vcodec', 'libx264'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "display(fig)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<video src=\"lorentz_attractor.mp4\" controls  >\n",
       "      Your browser does not support the <code>video</code> element.\n",
       "    </video>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Video object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import Video\n",
    "Video(filename)"
   ]
  }
 ],
